# BilingualBlog

The BilingualBlog card definition extends the base BlogPost card, adding a `translation` field that contains the blog post content translated to French.

## Import

To import the BilingualBlog code, use the following:

```js
import { BilingualBlog } from 'https://realms-staging.stack.cards/experiments/bilingual-blog/bilingual-blog';
```

## Define Field

The `translation` field is defined as a `contains(StringField)` field, which means it is an embedded field within the BilingualBlog card.

```js
@field translation = contains(StringField, {
  description: 'A full translation of the blog post body in French'
});
```

## Invoke Template

In templates, you can access the `translation` field using the fields API:

```hbs
<div class="translation">
  <@fields.translation />
</div>
```

## Dependencies

The BilingualBlog card definition depends on the following:

- `BlogPost` card definition
- `StringField` from the Boxel base API
- `Langugages` icon from the Boxel icon set

## Usage and Examples

The BilingualBlog card can be used anywhere a BlogPost card would be used, but with the added benefit of having a French translation of the post body available.

Here's an example of how you might use the BilingualBlog card:

```json
{
  "data": {
    "type": "card",
    "attributes": {
      "title": "Bienvenue sur notre blog!",
      "body": "Ceci est le contenu de notre premier article de blog bilingue.",
      "translation": "Welcome to our blog!\nThis is the content of our first bilingual blog post."
    },
    "meta": {
      "adoptsFrom": {
        "module": "./bilingual-blog",
        "name": "BilingualBlog"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

In this example, the `BilingualBlog` card is used to display a blog post with both the original French content and the English translation.
